### Continuous timeline root cause (Entry 31)

SDMA no-copy timeline:
- GEMM dur stays ~1.0 ms/stage
- AR dur is ~2.0 ms/stage
- AR-GEMM gap grows linearly from 0.011 ms to 24.568 ms by iter5/stage3

RCCL timeline:
- after transient, GEMM dur and AR dur both ~1.4-1.5 ms/stage
- AR-GEMM gap stays bounded ~0.5-0.6 ms

Mechanism: SDMA no-copy does not slow GEMM; GEMM outruns / starves SDMA AR.
stream_gemm produces stages every ~1.0ms while stream_ar consumes each stage
in ~2.0ms, causing backlog. Need improve SDMA AR service time under GEMM or
rebalance priority/CU so stage rates match.

