### Copy-pipe K1 hang + fix (Entry 55)

`MORI_SDMA_AG_COPY_PIPE=1` first run on `23b7978b` hung before K2:

```text
[STUCK] PE 4 K1 thr 0 scatter-wait sender=0 expected=4 got=3
[STUCK] PE 7 K1 thr 0 scatter-wait sender=0 expected=4 got=3
```

This is not a perf result. It means burst K1 scatter left the fourth qId=0
scatter signal short in the copy-pipe path. Fix `19192f89` scopes the remedy to
copy-pipe only: use `ScatterSdmaOnlyWaitEachChunkKernel`, which submit/waits
per chunk. Default baseline and Plan A still use burst `ScatterSdmaOnlyKernel`.

Entry 56 re-ran the wait-each-chunk K1 and still hung:

```text
[STUCK] PE 6 K1-chunked thr 0 chunk=3 scatter-wait sender=0 expected=4 got=3
```

Therefore `MORI_SDMA_AG_COPY_PIPE=1` is closed as correctness-failing for the
COPY-vs-RCCL target. It produced no valid perf data and is skipped by default in
`tools/bench_sdma_ag_copy_pipe.sh` unless `RUN_PIPE=1` is explicitly set. The
runtime path also requires `MORI_ALLOW_FAILED_COPY_PIPE=1`; `MORI_SDMA_AG_COPY_PIPE=1`
alone is ignored to avoid accidental hangs.

